    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-28T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="294"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/388: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-28T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 28, 1932—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 28—6:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_YWW1">Yen</persName> has written Secretary
                    General letter dated 26th which refers to Council’s decision concerning
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> report and
                    requests convocation of Assembly Committee of Nineteen to consider the duration
                    of the extension of 6 months’ period in accordance with resolution of July
                        1st.<note n="80" xml:id="d294fn80">See telegram No. 214, July 2, 9 p.m.,
                        from the Consul at Geneva, <ref target="#pg_127">p. 127</ref>.</note> Also
                    insists that Committee of Nineteen take steps to prevent Japan from aggravating
                    the situation in the meantime.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> says they will summon
                    Committee of Nineteen for a public session on Friday<note n="81"
                        xml:id="d294fn81">September 30.</note> as the request seems reasonable. The
                    Committee will probably explain to <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_YWW1"
                        >Yen</persName> why a definite duration cannot now be fixed but he does not
                    know what line will be taken on preventing Japan from aggravating the
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
